  "text": "Biosynthesis of Ag-NPs. TSB medium was prepared, sterilized, and inoculated with a fresh growth of P. aeruginosa ATCC 27853, being incubated at 37 ∘ C for 24 h. After the incubation time, the culture was centrifuged at 10,000 rpm and the culture supernatant was used for the synthesis of Ag-NPs. Different concentrations of P. aeruginosa culture supernatant [CITATION_1] 30 , and 50% by volume) were separately added to the reaction vessels containing silver nitrate at different concentrations (1, 5, and 10 mM).",
